<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 28 at 1:57PM CDT until August 28 at 2:30PM CDT by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 230 PM CDT
FOR SOUTHEASTERN JO DAVIESS...NORTH CENTRAL CARROLL AND WESTERN
STEPHENSON COUNTIES...
At 157 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Loran, or 12
miles northeast of Mount Carroll, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Bolton, Eleroy, Lena, Lake Le-Aqua-na State Park, Damascus,
Waddams Grove, Scioto Mills, Cedarville and Red Oak.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
